Key Match Events: Yussuf Poulsen created the opening goal and then added a brilliant second with an acrobatic bicycle kick as Denmark beat Serbia 2-0.
Albert Gronbaek Erlykke scored the first goal for Denmark in the 36th minute.
Yussuf Poulsen scored the second goal for Denmark in the 61st minute.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Denmark had 54.1% possession while Serbia had 45.9%.
Denmark had 3 shots on goal compared to Serbia's 2.
Denmark had 8 corner kicks while Serbia had 3.
The match was held at Parken in Copenhagen, Denmark with an attendance of 34,902.
